communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In July 2014, classical swine fever was reported from domestic swine in Tov province (see event summary at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=15533). The event was resolved on 7 Aug 2014; see final report at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=15932.

Selenge province is located in northern Mongolia, between Orkhon and Selenge river basin and forest steppe region with hills and mountains. It borders with Russia in the north, Bulgan and Orhon provinces to the west, Tov province to the south and Hentiy province to the east (http://www.toursmongolia.com/provinces/selenge).

See a map of Mongolia's administrative divisions at http://www.ephotopix.com/image/asia/mongolia_political_map.gif. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2952113,12597.]
